SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 423
By Haile
A RESOLUTION to honor Dr. Clint A. Satterfield on the occasion
of his retirement as Director of Schools for
Trousdale County.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing a
dedicated professional who has contributed significantly to the progress of public education
during his long and distinguished career; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Clint A. Satterfield is retiring from Trousdale County Schools after more
than forty years spent developing the county's students into responsible citizens with bright
futures; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Satterfield has positively impacted his community as Director of Schools
for Trousdale County since 2007, when he retired from coaching; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Satterfield created the unified vision and mission statement for the
school system, "Accelerating and Graduating All Students for the Careers of Tomorrow"; and
WHEREAS, under his leadership, Trousdale County has been recognized as one of the
top school districts in Tennessee since 2012 and was named School District of the Year by
SCORE in 2013 and 2015, thus becoming the only two-time winner in the history of the
prestigious award; and
WHEREAS, Trousdale County Schools achieved "Exemplary School" designations from
the Department of Education in 2012, 2019, 2022, 2023, and 2024, and all three of the county's
schools have been named "Reward Schools" in multiple school years; and
WHEREAS, Trousdale County was recognized as a "Best For All" school district in 2022
for its strategic spending of federal COVID-19 relief funds to improve student achievement, and
Trousdale County High School was honored as a National Blue Ribbon School in 2015; and
