WHEREAS, the son of Jim and Eleanor Satterfield, Dr. Satterfield began his illustrious
coaching career in 1983 as an assistant football coach at Trousdale County High School; he
was promoted to the role of head coach in 1984, thus beginning a distinguished twenty-four-
year tenure; and
WHEREAS, throughout his career, Dr. Satterfield not only followed but also built upon
the legacy of his father, Jim Satterfield, a fellow TSSAA Hall of Fame inductee and respected
football coach at Trousdale County; under Dr. Clint Satterfield's guidance, his teams amassed
an impressive record of 239 wins against only 61 losses, an astounding winning percentage of
eighty percent; and
WHEREAS, his dedication to Trousdale County High School athletics and his
Yellowjacket teams yielded five TSSAA State championships (1990, 1993, 1997, 1998, and
2005) and set a high standard for future generations; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Satterfield's influence extended beyond the high school level, as he
spent seventeen years as a football coach at Satterfield Middle School, which is named in honor
of his father, a designation that speaks to the family's deep ties to the sport and the community;
and
WHEREAS, in addition to his football coaching responsibilities, Dr. Satterfield
contributed significantly as the athletic director at Trousdale County for seven years and as the
head baseball coach from 1988 to 1991; and
WHEREAS, named State Coach of the Year numerous times, Dr. Satterfield received
the prestigious A. F. Bridges Award in 2000, an honor that further demonstrates his remarkable
achievements and dedication to excellence and sportsmanship; and
WHEREAS, his induction into the TSSAA Hall of Fame in 2016 is a fitting tribute to his
contributions to TSSAA and high school sports in Tennessee, as it celebrates a legacy that
encompasses both winning records and the shaping of character in young athletes; and
